{
    "word": "Infidelity",
    "definitions": [
        "Lack of faith or belief in some religious system; especially, a lack of faith in, or disbelief of, the inspiration of the Scriptures, of the divine origin of Christianity.",
        "Unfaithfulness to the marriage vow or contract; violation of the marriage covenant by adultery.",
        "Breach of trust; unfaithfulness to a charge, or to moral obligation; treachery; deceit; as, the infidelity of a servant."
    ],
    "examples": [
        "There is, indeed, no doubt but that vanity is one of the principal causes of infidelity."
    ],
    "etymology": "[L. infidelitas: cf. F. infid.]"
